      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW TARKOV (5) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at Sandown in a handy 29.62 beating Ash Intention. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Looks to have an edge on most of these. PAW RAYNOR (1) could manage only fourth at Sandown last time but turned heads when posting a fast 25.19 over 450m at Ballarat the start prior. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. CHEEKY MEEKI (2) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Ballarat behind PAW TARKOV (25.39) in a Grade 5 H. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from her last run stacks up well. Expecting another good run. RIPPED PAIGE (4) cannot be ruled out.",
